features: 💕[Freestanding Structure]:A sturdy metal frame is embedded in the top edges of the HomeHacks hamper basket so the laundry basket stands firmly upright even when empty.

💕[Extra Large Capacity]:The laundry hamper measures 15.7" x 11.8"x 24.4" (L x W x H) with 75L large capacity. This clothes basket can hold clothes, pillows, baby toys, etc. Good choice for campus dorms or family life.

💕[Double reinforced Handles]:Two long handles, one on each side of the tall hamper, are reinforced with durable tight stitching to prevent tearing. Handles are long enough to hold for easy carrying with one or two hands, even when hamper is full of laundry or other items.

💕[Premium Fabric]:The extra-large laundry basket is made of premium cotton and flax material. PEVA waterproof coating inside of the basket keeps clothes dry and makes cleaning easy--simply wipe clean with a damp sponge or cloth. Attention: Do not clean in washing machine. Coating is not resistant to washing machine.
💕[Portable Collapsible]:The collapsible laundry bin folds up easily for compact storage, ideal for home, campus, camping, apartments, hotels and shopping.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ultimate Laundry Organization Solution!

These waterproof, freestanding laundry hampers are a game-changer.First and foremost, the size is impressive. With ample room to hold loads of laundry, these baskets are perfect for families or anyone who deals with a significant amount of clothing. The collapsible design is genius, allowing you to effortlessly store them when not in use and saving precious space.The waterproof feature is a real game-changer. Accidental spills or damp clothes won't pose a problem anymore. This feature not only protects the baskets but also prevents any potential messes from spreading to your floors.The freestanding design adds to the convenience. No more struggling with laundry bags that fall over or baskets that need constant propping up. These hampers stay upright and sturdy, making laundry sorting a breeze.I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of the materials. The baskets are built to withstand the demands of regular use, and the reinforced handles make carrying heavy loads much easier.Whether you're organizing a laundry room, a bedroom, or even a dorm, the HomeHacks 2-Pack Large Laundry Basket is a must-have. The value of having two baskets in one pack is unbeatable, allowing you to keep different types of laundry separate or to have one in multiple locations.In a world where home organization is key, these laundry baskets truly shine. They've simplified my laundry routine and added a touch of efficiency to my home. If you're seeking a laundry solution that's practical, durable, and space-saving, don't miss out on these baskets. They're an investment in a more organized and hassle-free lifestyle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great hamper/laundry basket.
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to get away from the standard hard plastic type hampers because they don't store well when not being used. And when they start to break there is no fixing them unless you want to use a bunch of duck tape. These are sturdy. They are lined so no wetness leaks through. They fold easily for storage. I keep one in my bath room to use as a hamper but the other two only get used on laundry day. They hold quite a bit and look nice, too. I'm really happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value. More durable than expected.
reviews.reviewText: These are great. They probably won't last forever, but they are much more durable than I expected and have strongly attached straps. I live in a 3 story house with the bedrooms at the top and laundry at the bottom, and I tend to overload laundry bins. So I've eventually had the straps/ handles break on every laundry basket I've ever owned, and recently decided to try a new strategy of buying lots of cheap bins instead of a few more expensive bins. These have held for 3 months so far, and I feel that I've already gotten my money's worth.I also really like my new set up of having more bins than I need. These are so cheap and fold up when not in use, so I can always keep an empty one nearby, and then I never have the problem of clothes piling up on the floor while I'm in the process of doing laundry.
